(Babesia gibsoni is blood protozoa that parasitize erythrocytes causing anemia in the infected dog\056 It is one of the most common tick born) Tj
T*
(infection that is transmitted by the ticks present on the dog skin\056 Babesia gibsoni hemolytic anemia\054 thrombocytopenia\054 lethargy and) Tj
T*
(splenomegaly\056 In many cases\054 treatment is frustrating\054 low levels of parasites remain and a chronic subclinical carrier state develops\056) Tj
