(Babesia Vogeli is one of the main cause of Babesiosis in Dog\056 The protozoa is transmitted by Rhipicephalus Sanguineus ticks which has a) Tj
T*
(global distribution but is most prevalent in tropical and subtropical regions\056 Babesia Vogeli is regarded as being only mildly pathogenic) Tj
T*
(causing subclinical or only mild disease\056 B\056 Vogeli infections\054 severe complications can develop in dogs infected with other species including) Tj
T*
(systemic inflammatory response syndrome \050SIRS\051\054 multiple organ dysfunction syndrome \050MODS\051\054 refractory hypotension and septic shock\056) Tj
