(Babesia rossi is blood protozoa that parasitize erythrocytes causing anemia in the infected dog\056 It is one of the most common ticks born) Tj
T*
(infection that is transmitted by the ticks present on the dog skin\056 The protozoa get transmitted by Haemaphysalis elliptica and possibly H\056) Tj
T*
(leachi\056 Babesia rossi causes peracute and acute disease\054 the clinical signs including pale mucous membranes\054 depression\054 tachycardia\054) Tj
T*
(tachypnoea\054 anorexia\054 weakness\054 splenomegaly and fever\056 The clinical signs are attributed to tissue hypoxia resulting from anaemia and a) Tj
T*
(concomitant systemic inflammatory response syndrome caused by marked cytokine release\056 The severe form of the disease is characterised by) Tj
T*
(haemolytic anaemia and severe acid\055base derangements with secondary multiple organ failure and complications such as acute renal failure\054) Tj
T*
(hepatopathy with marked icterus\054 hypoglycaemia acute respiratory distress syndrome\054 cerebral pathology and additional immune\055mediated) Tj
T*
(erythrocyte destruction\056 Mortality is around 12\045\056 A feature of the disease is that\054 in contrast to babesiosis in other domestic species\054 pups and) Tj
T*
(immature dogs are also badly affected\056) Tj
