(Babesia canis is blood protozoa that parasitize erythrocytes causing anaemia in the infected dog\056 It is one of the most common infections that) Tj
T*
(is transmitted by the ticks present on the dog skin\056 Babesia canis is thought to cycle primarily between domestic dogs and Rhipicephalus) Tj
T*
(sanguineus the brown tick\056 Cases of canine babesiosis may present with wide variation of severity of clinical signs\054 ranging from a) Tj
T*
(hyperacute\054 shock\055associated\054 hemolytic crisis to an inapparent\054 subclinical infection) Tj
T*
